{
  "q1_accurate": [
    {"tool": "sense_status", "query": "(no args)", "note": "key_symbols named doltdb.DoltDB (194 refs) and cli.CliContext (262 refs) immediately, which is how I identified the core object in Step 1 without any exploration"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "doltdb.DoltDB", "note": "gave the struct at doltdb.go:126 plus composed_by list — env.DoltEnv:82, env.DbData:59, sqle.Database:76, sqle.DoltDatabaseProvider:55, cluster.commithook:36, dsess.dbRoot:92 and ~35 dtables holders — all cited verbatim in Step 4"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "doltdb.DoltDB", "note": "retained_via_interfaces (53 rows) directly produced Step 5 in full: dbfactory.singletonDB file.go:89, gitRemoteCacheEntry git_remote.go:99, commands.singletonDBCache transfer.go:263, main.LocalCSCache cscache.go:31, datas.database rootTracker database_common.go:37, commitgraph.entry/topoIter/dotDotIter, clusterdb ClusterStatusProvider holders, gcctx.GCSafepointController:26 — none of which name DoltDB"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "engine.SqlEngine", "note": "inherits cli.Queryist (command.go:103) and composes sqle.DoltDatabaseProvider — the exact edge that makes the Queryist route in Step 3/Step 5 item 1 real"},
    {"tool": "sense_search", "query": "chunk store root hash commit swap storage root", "note": "returned chunks.ChunkStore.Root:111, Commit:116, Rebase:107, nbs.GenerationalNBS.Root:307, nbs.NomsBlockStore.Root:1548 — the layer table in Step 2"},
    {"tool": "sense_search", "query": "late binding queryist build sql engine local process", "note": "pinned commands.newLateBindingEngine utils.go:234, cli.LateBindQueryist cli_context.go:57, main.buildLateBinder dolt.go:636 — hops 1-3 of Step 3"}
  ],
  "q1_wrong": [
    {"tool": "sense_search", "query": "core database object commands and sessions operate through", "note": "near-total miss — top hits were nbs.filterJournalCore, sqlserver.logrusZapCore, git.GitAPI.HashObject; keyword matching on the literal token 'core' drowned the concept. I got the actual answer from sense_status key_symbols in the same parallel call, not from this search"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "doltdb.DoltDB", "note": "retained_via_interfaces included test-only rows (types.badVersionStore value_store_test.go:374, chunks.TestStoreView test_utils.go:40) despite include_tests:false, and several carrier attributions are visibly wrong — cluster.remotesrvStore is listed as the carrier for types.ValueStore.cs, tree.nodeStore.store and chunks.CSMetricWrapper.cs, which is not a containment path that exists. I had to re-derive those carriers by reading the structs"}
  ],
  "q2_fallbacks": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "doltdb.DoltDB", "fallback": "read", "missing": "rows give the holder's ref line (struct declaration) but not the field line or field name — I needed 'file:line of the retaining field' per the ticket, so I read/sed every struct: sqle.Database.ddb database.go:80, cluster.commithook.srcDB commithook.go:50, hooksFiringRemoteSrvStore.ddb remotesrv.go:88, AutoGCController.hooks auto_gc.go:96, prollyStats.ddb stats_kv.go:212"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "doltdb.DoltDB", "fallback": "read", "missing": "the 'chain' strings are declared containment only and several were wrong (see q1_wrong); to write Step 5 mechanically I read database_common.go:37-67 to confirm rt is a rootTracker satisfied by *types.ValueStore, and cscache.go:25-85 to confirm LocalCSCache holds NBS stores"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "doltdb.DoltDB", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "response was truncated with 98 omitted_edges and 29 low_confidence_hidden, and dsess.DoltSession / DatabaseSessionState / branchState never appeared as holders even though branchState.dbData is the session's route to DoltDB — I grepped 'type DoltSession struct' and 'type branchState struct' to get session.go:48-75 and database_session_state.go:102-124"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "doltdb.DoltDB", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "no storage-side coverage of nbs internals; I grepped 'type NomsBlockStore struct' and 'type GenerationalNBS struct' to get store.go:96-126 and generational_chunk_store.go:40-44 for the Step 2 layer table"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "doltdb.DoltDB", "fallback": "read", "missing": "no test inventory (affected_tests was empty, tests_affected_count 0) despite a doltdb_test.go edge showing in sense_graph — I ls'd *_test.go across doltdb/, sqle/, sqle/cluster/, nbs/, dsess/, dbfactory/, engine/ to build the Step 7 test map"}
  ],
  "q3_hints": [
    {"tool": "sense_status", "query_before": "core database object commands and sessions operate through", "query_after": "doltdb.DoltDB", "hint": "key_symbols listing 'doltdb.DoltDB, class, type DoltDB struct, references 194' — the status fingerprint corrected a failed semantic search and set the symbol for every subsequent graph/blast call"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query_before": "doltdb.DoltDB (sense_graph, depth 1)", "query_after": "doltdb.DoltDB (sense_blast, max_hops 3, include_tests false)", "hint": "next_steps: {tool: sense_blast, symbol: doltdb.DoltDB, reason: '82 callers found — check blast radius before changing this symbol'} — I ran blast in the same turn, and its retained_via_interfaces block is what made Steps 4-5 possible"}
  ],
  "q4_value": "The retained_via_interfaces block on sense_blast(doltdb.DoltDB). The entire premise of the ticket was 'find holders whose field is typed as a narrow interface so the file never names DoltDB' — dbfactory.singletonDB (file.go:89) holding a datas.Database, main.LocalCSCache (cscache.go:31) holding remotesrv.RemoteSrvStore, commitgraph.entry (commitgraph.go:89) holding a HashResolver, gcctx.GCSafepointController (gc_safepoint_controller.go:26) keyed on GCRootsProvider. Grepping 'DoltDB' finds none of these; grepping every interface name in a 22k-symbol Go repo and hand-resolving satisfiers was not doable in this session's budget. That one field turned a multi-hour audit into one call.",
  "q5_improve": "Make retained_via_interfaces emit the field line and field name, not just the holder's declaration ref — 'go/libraries/doltcore/sqle/cluster/commithook.go:50 srcDB *doltdb.DoltDB' instead of 'commithook.go:36'. Every holder in the audit needed the field line, so I read ~20 structs purely to convert refs into field lines. Second: fix or confidence-flag the 'carrier' attribution, since cluster.remotesrvStore was listed as the carrier for types.ValueStore.cs and tree.nodeStore.store, which is not a real containment path and would have been a wrong citation if I had trusted it.",
  "score": 8,
  "score_rationale": "The retained_via_interfaces set (Q1) handed me holders like dbfactory.singletonDB and gcctx.GCSafepointController that no grep for 'DoltDB' would ever surface, and the status→graph→blast hint chain (Q3) recovered from a failed semantic search in one turn — but truncated graph output that omitted the entire dsess session chain, missing field lines, and visibly wrong carrier attributions (Q2) meant roughly half my citations still came from reads and greps on top of Sense, which is exactly the 7-8 band rather than 9-10."
}

